<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Harry on 05-07-2002 09:24 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">First thing to say: This is a game I will really love. Very well done Larian!!!!

Things I like:
- the games runs very good on my AMD 300MHz with Voodoo2 and 256MB RAM.....in 800x600 with very high details settings! Great work!
- the graphics....what do I say? They are breathtaking. They are so detailed and colours are fine tuned. I have to think hard to remember a similar game with so good graphics.
- dialogs and speech are very well done too.
- the "pause" function: combat playes like a turnbased game, but better...you can play in realtime if you have easy opponets. A great improvement, to what you have to do, to kill those annoying 10 rats again in a turnbased game..  :)
- the mood of the game (one exception...see below)
- that I can put skills together at will
- and many more things...

Things I dislike:
- completly remove the blackout of unexplored area, please. This is not necessary. This kills some of the feeling to live in that world. Our avatar knows some things of the world, he is born in this world he have lived in this world....and most important..when I look somewhere where I have not been...I can still see the world...I don't see a black wall.  :) 
LOS is implemeted and a radius of "how far I can see". You can use the minimap/automap to track where I have been. And removing "the black" is easy done...look at those "cutscenes". You remove it there already.  :)...If you don't remove it...give me the cheat code to do so..  :)
- I doubt the usefulness of the "identify" skill. In the demo I have bought gloves and a rope with +1 to identify from Gregor. I can equip them when I need things to identify. They give me +2 to identify. So why should I ever put there expensive skillpoints in?
- I don't like the "know your enemy-skill" (forgot the correct name). Why not make the info on monsters dependent on experience/level/amount of kills ? In the demo so far I have discovered quickly what monsters to fear. In the "throphy" section, I can see how much HP aso. the monsters have. No skill point here... (so far)


Bugs:
- In the "diary-personal traits section" the resistance never gets updated, and other errors here.
- Alchemy lvl 1 allows putting herbs in potions. Alchemy lvl 2 allows mixing of potions. In the demo the readout of the skill is interchanged.
- sometimes when accessing the skills, the game froze...high activity on HD...after pressing the right mousebutton game unfreezes....strange


This is the biggest and best demo I have ever played....I'm a longtime spectator of what had  grown from Nordlandtrilogie-&gt;LMK-&gt;Divine Divinity. I think it is a good mix, and I'm looking forward to the full game.

And who said that this demo is for 10 hours?....Maybe the first time...but I have played it a second time...and will play it again.... *g*
Good work!</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
